The paper proposes a new method for multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on cooperative behavior among multiple agents, which is a common topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the centralized training with decentralized execution (CTDE) regime, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
